    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "John",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 17,
        "summary": "Jesus offers the great Intercessory Prayer\u2014He is glorified by gaining eternal life\u2014He prays for His Apostles and all the Saints\u2014He explains how the Father and Son are one.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "These words spake Jesus, and lifted up his eyes to heaven, and said, Father, the hour is come; glorify thy Son, that thy Son also may glorify thee:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 110
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Mission of.",
                        "start": 134,
                        "end": 141
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As thou hast given him power over all flesh, that he should give eternal life to as many as thou hast given him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of; Jesus Christ, Power of.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 6:37.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 10:29 (27\u201329); D&C 50:41.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And this is life eternal, that they might know thee the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom thou hast sent.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Eternal Life.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 1:2; 2:25; D&C 132:24.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 9:3; Hosea 2:20; 1\u00a0Jn. 4:8 (7\u20138); D&C 101:16. TG\u00a0God, Knowledge about; Objectives; Testimony.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godhead.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Messenger of the Covenant.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I have glorified thee on the earth: I have finished the work which thou gavest me to do.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 65:6; 76:43 (40\u201343).",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 19:2. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Atonement through.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now, O Father, glorify thou me with thine own self with the glory which I had with thee before the world was.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Celestial Glory; Jesus Christ, Glory of.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Foreordained; Man, Antemortal Existence of.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I have manifested thy name unto the men which thou gavest me out of the world: thine they were, and thou gavest them me; and they have kept thy word.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 8:53; 3\u00a0Ne. 15:19 (19\u201320).",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now they have known that all things whatsoever thou hast given me are of thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Relationships with the Father.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For I have given unto them the words which thou gavest me; and they have received them, and have known surely that I came out from thee, and they have believed that thou didst send me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 18:18; John 6:68. TG\u00a0Revelation.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 8:42; 16:28 (27\u201328, 30); Gal. 4:4.",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 121
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I pray for them: I pray not for the world, but for them which thou hast given me; for they are thine.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 27:14; 84:63.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And all mine are thine, and thine are mine; and I am glorified in them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now I am no more in the world, but these are in the world, and I come to thee. Holy Father, keep through thine own name those whom thou hast given me, that they may be one, as we are.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Purpose of.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Unity.",
                        "start": 172,
                        "end": 175
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 183,
                        "end": 187
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "While I was with them in the world, I kept them in thy name: those that thou gavest me I have kept, and none of them is lost, but the son of perdition; that the scripture might be fulfilled.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 6:39; 18:9.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 108
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 50:42.",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 124
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 27:32. TG\u00a0Damnation; Death, Spiritual, Second; Hell.",
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 150
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now come I to thee; and these things I speak in the world, that they might have my joy fulfilled in themselves.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Joy.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1358
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I have given them thy word; and the world hath hated them, because they are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I pray not that thou shouldest take them out of the world, but that thou shouldest keep them from the evil.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0World.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Refuge.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 87
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Evil.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worldliness.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Sanctify them through thy truth: thy word is truth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sanctification.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 4:13.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Sam. 7:28; Ps. 119:142. TG\u00a0Truth.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As thou hast sent me into the world, even so have I also sent them into the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And for their sakes I sanctify myself, that they also might be sanctified through the truth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Atonement through.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Neither pray I for these alone, but for them also which shall believe on me through their word;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 45:5.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That they all may be one; as thou, Father, art in me, and I in thee, that they also may be one in us: that the world may believe that thou hast sent me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "4\u00a0Ne. 1:17 (15\u201317); D&C 38:27.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godhead; God the Father, Elohim.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 35:2; Moses 6:68.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the glory which thou gavest me I have given them; that they may be one, even as we are one:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 2:20.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 93:3.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I in them, and thou in me, that they may be made perfect in one; and that the world may know that thou hast sent me, and hast loved them, as thou hast loved me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Perfection.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Love of.",
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Father, I will that they also, whom thou hast given me, be with me where I am; that they may behold my glory, which thou hast given me: for thou lovedst me before the foundation of the world.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O righteous Father, the world hath not known thee: but I have known thee, and these have known that thou hast sent me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Knowledge about.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I have declared unto them thy name, and will declare it: that the love wherewith thou hast loved me may be in them, and I in them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Preaching.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Name.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Love of.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Relationships with the Father.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}